    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Next Step On Global Warming</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bela Liptak letter on June 8 editorial on global warming calls for orderly conversion to inexhaustible energy sources</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>You are correct in stating that more conservation and improved efficiency will extend the life of our planet's exhaustible energy supplies (''A Stern Warning on Warming,'' editorial, June 8). Yet the only permanent solution is the orderly conversion to inexhaustible energy sources. The sooner we recognize that fact, the more time we will have to achieve a smooth transition.</p>
        <p>BELA LIPTAK  Stamford, Conn., June 8, 2001</p>
        <p>The writer is editor of Environmental Engineers' Handbook.</p>
      </block>
